{"can_edit": true, "from": {"name": "Micha\u00ebl Caron Couturier", "id": "1646843124"}, "revision": "10153006712615019", "updated_time": "2013-06-23T06:07:38+0000", "can_delete": true, "created_time": "2013-02-25T22:10:14+0000", "message": "<p><strong>Recommended distro to start :</strong></p><p><br /></p><p><strong>Linux Mint 13 Xfce</strong></p><p>&lt;a href=&quot;#&quot; role=button&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;#&quot; role=button&gt;http://www.linuxmint.com/release.php?id=18&lt;/a&gt;</p><p><br /></p><p><strong>32 bits or 64 bits :</strong></p><p><br /></p><p>Under 4Gb of ram 32 bits is better. At 4Gb or better, use 64 bits or a 32 bits PAE kernel that will allow to use the ram over 3,5Gb</p><p><br /></p><p><b>Setup :</b></p><div><span><br />&lt;a href=&quot;#&quot; role=button&gt;http://www.howtoforge.com/the-perfect-desktop-linux-mint-13-xfce&lt;/a&gt;<br /><br /></span></div><p><strong>Easy suggestion to make it even more lightweight and fast :</strong></p><p><br /></p><p>sudo apt-get install openbox obconf</p><p>Then follow this tutorial :</p><p>&lt;a href=&quot;#&quot; role=button&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;#&quot; role=button&gt;http://openbox.org/wiki/Help:XFCE/Openbox&lt;/a&gt;<br /></p><p><br /></p><p><b>More into it :</b><br /><br />&lt;a href=&quot;#&quot; role=button&gt;http://ubuntuguide.org/wiki/Ubuntu_Precise&lt;/a&gt;<br /></p><p><br /></p><p><strong>Troubleshooting advice :</strong></p><p><br /></p><p>Use Google and seek for keywords related to your problem and the word Ubuntu. Ubuntu being the base distro of Mint, this will give out more results to help you.</p><p><br /></p><p>Use Google translate to seek for the amazing french documention of Ubuntu that may be fairly decent for beginners also.</p><p><br /></p><p>&lt;a href=&quot;#&quot; role=button&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;#&quot; role=button&gt;http://www.linuxquestions.org/&lt;/a&gt;</p><p>http://www.askubuntu.com</p><p><br /></p><p>&lt;a href=&quot;#&quot; role=button&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;#&quot; role=button&gt;http://doc.ubuntu-fr.org/&lt;/a&gt; (french)  or</p><p><strong>https://wiki</strong>.<strong>ubuntuusers</strong>.de/ (german)</p><p>&#123;source of advices about &quot;pure&quot; Ubuntu-distros <strong>&lt;a href=&quot;#&quot; role=button&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;#&quot; role=button&gt;http://wiki.ubuntuusers.de/Einsteiger&lt;/a&gt; </strong>&#125;</p><p><br /></p><p><em><strong>*Xfce is the base of most of the LTS of Ubuntu and Linux Mint. It is stable, well featured and lightweight enough for any use*</strong></em></p><p><br /></p><p><em><strong>*LTS releases have 5 years of desktop and server support, including 2 years for new hardware  support, regular releases only get 9 months of support without added  hardware support*</strong></em></p><p><br /></p><p><em><strong>*Mint is taken for codecs, flash, java usable from the live dvd/usb so it&#039;s pretty useful*</strong></em></p>", "subject": "Recommendations for beginners", "id": "10152649184365019", "icon": "https://fbstatic-a.akamaihd.net/rsrc.php/v2/yi/r/-64q65AWgXb.png"}